gomodel:SYNGO_867  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: By tissue fractionation of mouse whole brain [Fig2] or human post mortem hippocampus [Fig3], DTNBP1 (Dysbindin-1) is found concentrated in the synaptosome and synaptic vesicle fractions, with little protein in the PSD fraction. Immuno-EM (qualitative) confirmed postsynaptic density localisation in the dentate gyrus hilus [Fig6B & D] mossy fiber synapse [Fig7] and in the CA1 area of mouse [Fig8D & E].. Experimental description: Mouse, macaque and human material is used, as specified in figure legends:\nFig2: mouse, Fig3 human, Fig6 mouse, Fig 7 mouse, Fig8A macaque, Fig8B-E mouse. All endogenous protein.\n\n19/6/2017 Pim\n- A wealth of species is used in this paper. I have selected *mouse* as annotated species because biochem data and EM data are both available for this species." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2017-06-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_867" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

